Step 1. Framing the Problem - Describe the goal of this report.

This Lab aims to explore the linear relationship between population factors and median house prices in the California Housing Prices Dataset. Focus on three independent variables(median income, population, and number of households) and do univariate linear regression. By building and evaluating these models, we can compare the differences between models. Further analyze and make predictions about the market house prices.

Step 2. Getting the Data - hyperlink to the source and load into Pandas.

In[1]:
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.datasets import fetch_california_housing

# Get the California housing dataset
housing = fetch_california_housing(as_frame=True)

# Combine features (independent variables) and target (dependent variable) into a DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame(data=housing.data, columns=housing.feature_names)
df['median_house_value'] = housing.target

# Display the first few rows of the DataFrame
print(df.head())

(2) Create three Seaborn scatter plots of median house value vs. median income, population, and number of households.

In[12]:
# Set the style for seaborn plots
sns.set_style("whitegrid")

# Create the first scatter plot: Median House Value vs. Median Income
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.scatterplot(x='MedInc', y='median_house_value', data=df, alpha=0.6)
plt.title('Median House Value vs. Median Income', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Median Income (in $10,000)', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Median House Value (in $100,000)', fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Create the second scatter plot: Median House Value vs. Population
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.scatterplot(x='Population', y='median_house_value', data=df, alpha=0.6)
plt.title('Median House Value vs. Population', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Population', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Median House Value (in $100,000)', fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Create the third scatter plot: Median House Value vs. Number of Households
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.scatterplot(x='AveOccup', y='median_house_value', data=df, alpha=0.6)
plt.title('Median House Value vs. Number of Households', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Number of Households', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Median House Value (in $100,000)', fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
